<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-173] JOIN in subselect generates bad SQL</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-173</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As reported at openjpa-dev &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, the following query generates invalid SQL:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    UPDATE Email e SET e.totalDeliveries = e.totalDeliveries + 1&lt;br/&gt;
    WHERE e.email IN (&lt;br/&gt;
        SELECT m.email FROM MailingList l JOIN l.subscribers m)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OpenJPA (0.9.6) parses this correctly, but can&apos;t seems to be missing the JOIN clause or some table names from the generated SQL:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; org.apache.openjpa.lib.jdbc.ReportingSQLException: ERROR: syntax error at or near &quot;WHERE&quot; &lt;/p&gt;
{prepstmnt 27475707 UPDATE FB_EMAILS SET totalDeliveries = (totalDeliveries + ?) WHERE email IN (SELECT DISTINCT t2.email FROM WHERE (t2.email IN (SELECT t3.email FROM FB_EMAILS t3 WHERE t0.id = t1.id AND t1.subscribers_email = t3.email))) [params=(long) 1]}
&lt;p&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;code=0, state=42601&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    org.apache.openjpa.lib.jdbc.LoggingConnectionDecorator.wrap(LoggingConnectionDecorator.java:188)&lt;br/&gt;
